            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20fingers%20of%20a%20human%20hand%20wrote%20on%20the%20plaster%20of%20the%20wall%2C%20King%20Belshazzar's%20face%20%22turned%20pale%20with%20fear.%20Such%20terror%20gripped%20him%20that%20his%20knees%20knocked%20together%20and%20his%20legs%20gave%20way%20beneath%20him%22%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E(Daniel%205%3A5-6).%20Even%20the%20bravest%20sinner%20is%20terrified%20before%20the%20pure%20revelation%20of%20God's%20justice.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EHow%20often%20people%20mock%20God%20as%20though%20He%20were%20some%20senile%20puppy%20hiding%20under%20the%20porch!%20Their%20ignorance%20only%20displays%20their%20lack%20of%20understanding%20of%20His%20long-suffering.%20Someone%20once%20said%2C%20%22Never%20mistake%20the%20long-suffering%20of%20God%20for%20His%20approval.%22%20Those%20who%20persist%20in%20wrongdoing%2C%20counting%20on%20God's%20mercy%20to%20overlook%20their%20sins%2C%20will%20one%20day%20be%20forced%20to%20account%20for%20their%20actions.%20%22Their%20destruction%20is%20their%20reward%20for%20the%20harm%20they%20have%20done%22%20(1%20Peter%202%3A13).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWhen%20Belshazzar%20touched%20the%20holy%20vessels%20of%20the%20temple%20of%20God%20(Daniel%205%3A3-4)%2C%20he%20crossed%20the%20line%20with%20God.%20He%20met%20the%20same%20fate%20as%20did%20the%20rebellious%20angels%2C%20the%20people%20of%20Noah's%20day%2C%20and%20Sodom%20and%20Gomorrah.%20Belshazzar%20pushed%20the%20mercy%20of%20God%20over%20the%20line%2C%20and%20God's%20mercy%20turned%20to%20judgment.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWalk%20before%20God%20in%20fear%20and%20trembling%2C%20for%20He%20is%20an%20awesome%20God.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
